nished this quest with the<br>
help of my guild, Imperial Guards on Druzzil Ro.<br>
<br>
Last battle was cake with 24 (were gearing up for a Zland<br>
kill) and only had 2-3 spider adds (repopped during the<br>
fight).  Had talked to the guide online before I did the turn-in<br>
just to make sure everything was peachy, and it all worked<br>
just fine.<br>
<br>
Thanks for all the help!  Love my earring!<br>
<br>
Gryfalia<br>
59 Templar of Brell<br>
Imperial Guards<br>
Druzzil Ro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubreaksmashdatroll.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BreaksmashDaTroll</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/13/02 3:00:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2545.topic&index=275>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Smithing</span><hr size=1>  Just finished quest. Smithing was at 175 wis str 255. Last battle was done with 12 peeps with a SK tanking (Ralanan so powa), was long fight but was easy.<br>
<br>
 Breaksmash<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukneesmasher.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kneesmasher</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/13/02 8:16:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2545.topic&index=276>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Smithing</span><hr size=1> Well, I finished my smithing tonight. I got my Dusted Star Metal and remaining Bone Dust back from the GM when the forge ate it and I contiunued my smithing.  Didn't have another failure and made all the combines with a smithing of 176. My strength was maxed during the smithing and Wisdom was at about 170.<br>
<br>
Turned in all the pieces to the wyvern and got back the Finished Naginata.  Now I just have to spend some time in Siren's Grotto to get a couple of flawless diamonds and it will be time to rev up the guild and grab a few folks to go kill the dragons.<br>
<br>
So let me make sure I have this straight.  <br>
<br>
1) I say the phrase: &quot;You are one but two. Your vengeance shall find a home.&quot;  I say this standing on the bone pile in the same spot I said &quot;Remember, Garzicor&quot;.<br>
<br>
2) I give the &quot;Ghostly Presence&quot; the Kromzek Blood when he spawns, being careful that he is, indeed, the one I am giving it to.  That causes Garzicor's Remains to spawn.<br>
<br>
3) Garzicor's Remains attacks me.  I kill him and he is relatively easy.<br>
<br>
4) Once Garzicor's Remains is killed, another ghostly dragon appears, &quot;Garzicor's Wrath&quot; and I have to kill it too. He's tougher with a strong Fear AoE.<br>
<br>
5) Once he dies, two more translucent dragons spawn that are on CoV faction, one at the original spot and one farther down the tunnel. I give each a flawless diamond in turn and receive back a &quot;Magical Blackened Diamond&quot; from each.<br>
<br>
6) I go to a forge, combine the two Magical Blackened Diamonds with the Finished Naginata. (Heaven help me if I fail THAT combine!)<br>
<br>
7) I take the final blade to Eldriaks Fe'Dhar and give it to him. He gives it back and I have finally receive the Ethereal Bladed Naginata....FINALLY!<br>
<br>
Did I miss anything???  That final hand in to Eldriaks is necessary? Or no? I'm after the weapon, not the earring or other item.<br>
<br>
Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>
Dwarven Knight<br>
Torvonnilous Server<br>
<br>
&quot;Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ualliliel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alliliel</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_cyanspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/14/02 8:57:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2545.topic&index=277>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Smithing</span><hr size=1> Yes, the steps in Iustus' walkthru are correct. It's all very straightforward.<br>
<br>
Just to nitpick: from the 2 COV dragons at the end, one gives you a Magical Blackened Diamond, the other gives you back something with a slightly different name like a Magical Golden Diamond.<br>
<br>
Yes, when you do the final smithing, you get the completed weapon. I don't **think** you gain anything by turning it back into Eldriaks except some free xp. (I went and killed a kromzek first, just to make sure I was still max ally before this final turn in.)<br>
<br>
When turning your item into &quot;a ghostly presence&quot; make sure you see the name on the trade window.  Look <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.alliliel.com/garzicor/vial.jpg">here</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> to see a picture of this.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udesp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Desp</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/14/02 9:26:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2545.topic&index=278>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Smithing</span><hr size=1> I have a question about one part of this... You combine a small block of clay with a flask of water in the pottery wheel... Then you combine this with the complete raw blade in the pottery wheel????? I think that is what is supposed to be done but it wont let me combine these two items... Any help would be appreciated.<br>
<br>
-Despim 60 Savagelord - Legacy of Steel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unightgod.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NightGod</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/14/02 9:46:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2545.topic&index=279>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Smithing</span><hr size=1> Did you do the hammer + completed blade in the forge one last time before you tried the raw blade + clay in the pottery wheel?<br>
<br>
Give it a shot, with DNC gone, ya can't lose it to a bad combine-I personally forgot that combine myself, had to run back to the forge, then back to the kiln. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ughitming.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ghitming</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/15/02 12:05:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2545.topic&index=280>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Smithing</span><hr size=1> Finally successful!<br>
<br>
First failure - BS 179 failed Core Combine<br>
Second Failure - BS 185 failed blade fold 2<br>
Third Failure - BS 192 failed blade fold 1<br>
<br>
All attempts were made with STR 255, INT 201.<br>
<br>
For my successful run, I also had Boon of Garou on.  This gave me a Dex of 255 also.  Not sure if this had anything to do with it, but might as well throw it on.  Be careful because it can make you KOS in some zones.<br>
<br>
Thanks to the Claw of Nagafen and especially Merci for their help.<br>
<br>
Ghitming<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unightgod.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NightGod</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/15/02 12:40:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2545.topic&index=281>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Smithing</span><hr size=1> For the record, VI (Yak) and the people over at EQTraders(through testing) have confirmed that stats ONLY make a difference on skill ups. Your skill level alone determines your success/failure. Everything else along this line is as authentic as the old wive's tale that having the smithing book in an open inventory slot boosts your success rate. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukneesmasher.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kneesmasher</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/15/02 12:41:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2545.topic&index=282>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Flawless Diamonds?</span><hr size=1> What mobs in Siren's Grotto tend to drop the Flawless Diamonds?  I've heard it's the Sirens...but haven't been in the zone much. <br>
<br>
I plan to be spending some time there this week in hopes of getting a few drops.  Any hints would be greatly appreciated!<br>
<br>
Once I have the Flawless Diamonds, I can move ahead with the Dragon Spawning! <br>
<br>
OMG!! Is that a light at the end of this llloooonnnggggg quest tunnel?? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I hope it's not friggin TRAIN!<br>
<br>
Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>
Dwarven Knight<br>
Torvonnilous Server<br>
<br>
&quot;Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukneesmasher.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kneesmasher</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/16/02 9:34:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2545.topic&index=283>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> How tough is WRATH?</span><hr size=1> Can some one give me a comparison on the toughness of Garzicor's Wrath? Is he Wuoshi tough? Trakanon tough? Talendor tough? Gorenaire tough? Zlandicar tough? Dozekar tough?<br>
<br>
What is his AoE?  I know he fears, but what else? Cold? Fire? Poison? Disease?<br>
<br>
The guy claiming to have done him with one group...makes me think he is even less than Wuoshi tough, but I mention Wuoshi because he has a pretty strong fear.  My guild does Wuoshi with about 20 folks. Gorenaire with about 24 if we have the right Nukers on.  Dozekar takes a full guild turn-out, but he can't be anywhere near Doze.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Does the Dragon's Bane Nuke work on these Dragons?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
I got my 2 flawless diamonds and I'm about ready to spawn these muthers!<br>
<br>
